Fix uncommenting with irregular white spaces (#82)

Allow stripping white spaces on the left and right independently.
Also, make sure the stripping is not reverted by subsequent lines
which do have white spaces.

The following cases were broken and is now fixed:

Before this change:

1. ^//foo$    -> ^oo$
   ^// bar$      ^bar$
2. ^/*foo */$ -> ^foo $
3. ^/* foo*/$ -> ^/* /1* foo*/ */$

After this change:

1. ^//foo$    -> ^foo$
   ^// bar$      ^ bar$
2. ^/*foo */$ -> ^foo$
3. ^/* foo*/$ -> ^foo$

commentary.vim 1.3

* Provide :Commentary command.
* Provide gc text object.
* Support comments with no leading space.
* Preserve whitespace in b:commentary_format.
* Allow disabling backslash maps.
* Fix count with linewise map.
* Don't trigger modelines after commenting.
* Deprecation warnings.

Support comments with no leading space

Closes https://github.com/tpope/vim-commentary/issues/40

Use setlocal in the filetype example

Using local is problematic with multiple buffers/windows, e.g.:

- You have the auto-command configured for cmake files, where the
  comment string is set to '#'
- You split your main window into 2 side-by-side ones
- In the left window you open a C++ file
- In the right window you open a cmake file
- voila, the wrong comment string is then used when commenting out stuff
  with commentary commands in the left window

Preserve whitespace in b:commentary_format

Closes #33.
Remove debugging short circuit

Let Commentary be used as a command

This lets us do things like `:g/TODO/Commentary` or `:.,'aCommentary`

Closes #28.
Fix count with gcc

Comment text object

Closes #17.
